545
00:35:26,406 --> 00:35:28,800
Well...

546
00:35:31,208 --> 00:35:34,100
Melinda Gordon?

547
00:35:34,908 --> 00:35:37,601
Wow. I mean, yeah.

548
00:35:37,707 --> 00:35:40,803
Sorry to just show up like this.

549
00:35:40,905 --> 00:35:43,400
Rick came to see me in the hospital.

550
00:35:43,505 --> 00:35:46,600
Uh, sorry.
Professor Payne.

551
00:35:46,706 --> 00:35:49,100
He told me how you found me.

552
00:35:49,205 --> 00:35:50,802
He did?

553
00:35:50,908 --> 00:35:53,201
Yeah.

554
00:35:53,905 --> 00:35:57,501
He said you saved my life.

555
00:35:58,005 --> 00:35:58,902
Yeah.

556
00:35:59,008 --> 00:36:02,600
Um, do you want to come in?

557
00:36:07,608 --> 00:36:11,503
Uh, Rick said he was with you...

558
00:36:13,105 --> 00:36:16,701
That you knew I was in trouble?

559
00:36:16,807 --> 00:36:20,403
And he said you knew things
about Martin Schaer.

560
00:36:20,505 --> 00:36:23,201
He said he couldn't tell me
what you knew, just...

561
00:36:23,308 --> 00:36:26,302
I had to ask you.

562
00:36:27,606 --> 00:36:29,900
Did... did you know Martin?

563
00:36:30,005 --> 00:36:31,700
I know him, yes.

564
00:36:31,808 --> 00:36:35,300
You were with him when he died.

565
00:36:35,406 --> 00:36:38,402
It was my fault.

566
00:36:40,408 --> 00:36:43,601
I knew he was sick.
I should have kept him from going.

567
00:36:43,707 --> 00:36:47,300
Do you think you could have?

568
00:36:47,408 --> 00:36:50,700
You don't understand.

569
00:36:51,908 --> 00:36:54,602
I left him.

570
00:36:55,305 --> 00:36:58,001
I left him.

571
00:37:01,408 --> 00:37:03,202
The guards were moving too fast.

572
00:37:03,307 --> 00:37:04,802
I can't see where they went.

573
00:37:04,908 --> 00:37:08,000
Marty, I see some.

574
00:37:08,305 --> 00:37:10,803
It's right here.
We found it.

575
00:37:10,906 --> 00:37:12,900
Marty, are you ok?

576
00:37:13,005 --> 00:37:14,401
Marty.

577
00:37:14,505 --> 00:37:16,101
Uh! Ok. Marty.

578
00:37:16,205 --> 00:37:17,103
Come on.

579
00:37:17,206 --> 00:37:18,702
We can't stop here.

580
00:37:18,806 --> 00:37:20,300
Wait. Wait.

581
00:37:20,406 --> 00:37:23,302
No. No.
We're going back.

582
00:37:23,408 --> 00:37:25,601
Ok.

583
00:37:25,708 --> 00:37:28,502
Penn, it's ok. I'm ok.
It's ok. I just--

584
00:37:28,606 --> 00:37:29,800
We have to go back.

585
00:37:29,907 --> 00:37:33,701
- This is the only time we can do this.
- No. No. We have to go back.

586
00:37:33,805 --> 00:37:36,801
Will you hold...

587
00:37:38,807 --> 00:37:41,202
I want you to go.

588
00:37:41,306 --> 00:37:43,002
Go back the way we came.

589
00:37:43,108 --> 00:37:46,002
I'll wait here.

590
00:37:49,708 --> 00:37:53,001
I love you.

591
00:37:53,005 --> 00:37:56,903
I'll be here when you get back.

592
00:37:57,405 --> 00:37:59,601
Ok.

593
00:37:59,905 --> 00:38:02,402
I'll go back. I'll bring help.

594
00:38:02,506 --> 00:38:04,403
I'll promise.

595
00:38:04,506 --> 00:38:06,000
I went back to camp as fast as I could,

596
00:38:06,106 --> 00:38:11,103
but he wasn't where I'd left him
when we got back.

597
00:38:11,706 --> 00:38:15,600
We looked for him for two days.

598
00:38:19,905 --> 00:38:24,802
We were supposed to get married
when we got back.

599
00:38:25,508 --> 00:38:27,901
When I got back, I...

600
00:38:28,005 --> 00:38:29,901
I was so empty inside,

601
00:38:30,007 --> 00:38:31,301
all I could do was work.

602
00:38:31,405 --> 00:38:36,203
I couldn't stop to think. If I did,
I would think of him, and...

603
00:38:36,306 --> 00:38:42,501
and then I was getting all the credit
for things that we did together.

604
00:38:42,905 --> 00:38:47,501
I couldn't have done
any of it without him.

605
00:38:47,906 --> 00:38:50,400
And the university
insisted it was ok.

606
00:38:50,507 --> 00:38:55,003
The more famous the professor,
the more grant money for the university.

607
00:38:55,105 --> 00:38:59,503
He was sick for 3 days
before you left him.

608
00:38:59,606 --> 00:39:02,600
How do you know that?

609
00:39:02,705 --> 00:39:04,403
I've seen Martin.

610
00:39:04,508 --> 00:39:07,200
His spirit.

611
00:39:07,308 --> 00:39:09,800
He's here with us right now.

612
00:39:09,908 --> 00:39:11,102
I...

613
00:39:11,206 --> 00:39:13,402
I don't believe you.

614
00:39:13,507 --> 00:39:15,403
I didn't want to believe I was sick.

615
00:39:15,505 --> 00:39:18,801
There was so much work we had to do,
and there wasn't enough time to do it.

616
00:39:18,908 --> 00:39:22,300
He didn't want to say anything
about being sick because

617
00:39:22,408 --> 00:39:24,102
there was so much work
you had to do.

618
00:39:24,205 --> 00:39:26,803
And now she blames herself for
what happened, but there's nothing

619
00:39:26,905 --> 00:39:30,602
that could have saved me. It was
dengue fever. Mosquitoes carry it.

620
00:39:30,706 --> 00:39:33,000
He knows that you blame yourself,

621
00:39:33,106 --> 00:39:34,800
but he was already dying.

622
00:39:34,905 --> 00:39:36,603
He had dengue fever.

623
00:39:36,706 --> 00:39:43,401
I tried to make it back on my own,
but I wasn't thinking right,
and I got lost.

624
00:39:51,705 --> 00:39:54,902
I couldn't find her.

625
00:39:56,105 --> 00:39:59,503
When I finally couldn't walk anymore,
I just...

626
00:39:59,608 --> 00:40:02,702
I lay down to die.

627
00:40:03,607 --> 00:40:06,201
But I thought that...

628
00:40:06,308 --> 00:40:09,703
no matter what happened,

629
00:40:10,107 --> 00:40:13,501
I would always love her.

630
00:40:14,606 --> 00:40:18,302
He was thinking of you
when he died.

631
00:40:18,406 --> 00:40:22,702
He knew that he would
always love you.

632
00:40:24,206 --> 00:40:27,602
I'm so lost without you.

633
00:40:28,907 --> 00:40:30,802
Everywhere I go,

634
00:40:30,905 --> 00:40:32,801
everywhere I look,

635
00:40:32,908 --> 00:40:35,301
I can feel you.

636
00:40:35,405 --> 00:40:37,501
Us.

637
00:40:37,606 --> 00:40:41,102
You showed me everything.

638
00:40:41,507 --> 00:40:42,901
And now I don't want...

639
00:40:43,006 --> 00:40:47,202
I don't want to be here
without you.

640
00:40:48,905 --> 00:40:51,100
Please don't leave me.

641
00:40:51,205 --> 00:40:52,303
We were meant to be together.

642
00:40:52,405 --> 00:40:55,902
We were meant to show each other
the things we did, to teach each other,

643
00:40:56,005 --> 00:40:58,601
and now it's...
it's meant to be different.

644
00:40:58,706 --> 00:41:01,802
But nothing...
nothing can take it away.

645
00:41:01,905 --> 00:41:07,201
We'll both bring all of it
with us wherever we go next.

646
00:41:07,905 --> 00:41:10,501
I'll tell her.

647
00:41:10,607 --> 00:41:12,602
Tell her to keep working.

648
00:41:12,705 --> 00:41:14,302
But tell her she's got to
keep living, too,

649
00:41:14,407 --> 00:41:18,803
because one's no good
without the other.

650
00:41:20,708 --> 00:41:22,500
It's gonna be hard for him.

651
00:41:22,605 --> 00:41:23,802
Who?

652
00:41:23,906 --> 00:41:26,002
Rick Payne.

653
00:41:26,108 --> 00:41:29,400
It's gonna be hard for him
to stay so cynical now.

654
00:41:29,505 --> 00:41:32,501
He'll find a way.

655
00:41:42,908 --> 00:41:46,600
What is it?
What's happening?

656
00:41:47,807 --> 00:41:50,002
He's crossed over.

657
00:41:50,105 --> 00:41:52,702
He's gone.

658
00:41:57,306 --> 00:41:59,000
That's a good thing, right?

659
00:41:59,107 --> 00:42:02,501
Yeah, it's a good thing.

660
00:42:03,406 --> 00:42:04,401
Come on.

661
00:42:04,506 --> 00:42:09,202
Let's take a walk,
and we can talk some more.

662
00:42:37,506 --> 00:42:39,302
I had to come back and get my car.

663
00:42:39,405 --> 00:42:42,303
Find your keys?

664
00:42:44,208 --> 00:42:47,401
Martin crossed over.

665
00:42:48,705 --> 00:42:50,001
- He told me...
- Hold on.

666
00:42:50,108 --> 00:42:56,701
I need a moment to keep my knee-jerk
cynical reaction from ignoring
all other possibilities.

667
00:42:56,807 --> 00:42:58,803
Ok.

668
00:42:58,906 --> 00:43:00,201
Martin told you...

669
00:43:00,305 --> 00:43:03,201
That he was worried about you.

670
00:43:03,308 --> 00:43:06,903
He doesn't know how you're going to
be able to stay so cynical now.

671
00:43:07,007 --> 00:43:08,501
I'll find a way.

672
00:43:08,606 --> 00:43:11,101
Exactly.

673
00:43:14,807 --> 00:43:18,301
I think I might have been partially
inebriated the other night.

